A MAN accused of killing a Khayelitsha woman on her 21st birthday and burying her body beneath concrete in a neighbour's yard, confessed to the murder today, the NPA said.Monwabisi Mbombo (25) a magician and entertainer by trade, was accused of killing Anelisa Dulaze, who was missing for three months before her body was found in May 2016.Mbombo confessed to murdering Dulaze after they had sex in his home on 31 January, 2016.Dulaze wanted to leave when he allegedly forced her to stay with him, the court papers read.They argued before Mbombo pushed a bottle against Dulaze.Dulaze then fell and hit her head against the wall, where she died.Afterward, Mbombo went to a shebeen where he drank a bottle of vodka. When he returned to his home, he buried the body in a hole he dug on his neighbour's property where an apartment was being built.Mbombo accepted a five-year prison sentence for kidnapping and a 15-year year prison sentence for murder.Dulaze was a drama student who had been planning to return to Wits University to complete her studies after financial difficulties forced her to drop out.Her mother Vathiswa Dulaze said she finally had closure after her daughter's body was found. She said Mbombo went to school with her daughter, adding that Anelisa and her friends knew him "very well".&nbsp;http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/magician-confesses-to-killing-21-year-old-on-her-birthday-20170504